co.cask.cdap.api.plugin

Interface PluginConfigurer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DatasetConfigurer
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ApplicationConfigurer, HttpServiceConfigurer, MapReduceConfigurer, PipelineConfigurer, ServiceConfigurer, SparkConfigurer, WorkerConfigurer

    public interface PluginConfigurer
extends DatasetConfigurer
    This interface provides methods to register plugin usage in a CDAP Program. The registered plugins will be available at the runtime of the Program.

    • Method Detail

      • usePlugin

        @Nullable
<T> T usePlugin(String pluginType,
                       String pluginName,
                       String pluginId,
                       PluginProperties properties)
        Adds a Plugin usage to the Application and create a new instance. The Plugin will be accessible at execution time via the PluginContext.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the plugin class
        Parameters:
        pluginType - plugin type name
        pluginName - plugin name
        pluginId - an unique identifier for this usage. The same id is used to get the plugin at execution time.
        properties - properties for the plugin. The same set of properties will be used to instantiate the plugin instance at execution time
        Returns:
        A new instance of the plugin class or null if no plugin was found
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the pluginId has been used already
